                <note rend="inline" type="source">551.5F1/189: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-19T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 19, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>331. If participation of the great powers, especially the United States and Great
                    Britain, is assured, Mexico will probably issue a call to an international
                    conference on silver: the place, Mexico City; the time, this winter. This
                    Government distinctly favors the conference idea, and hopes that the British
                    will see fit to accept the invitation. Please sound them out on this matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
